    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Running `:!make install` for nvim (with LTO) itself shows:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[137/156] Generating it.mo\r\n\r\n.. [153/156] Linking C executable bin/nvim\r\n[154/156] Generating pack/dist/opt/vimball/doc/tags\r\n[155/156] Generating pack/dist/opt/matchit/doc/tags\r\n[156/156] Generating doc/tags\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt waits after the \"..\" for quite some time (due to the linking taking so long).\r\n\r\nI think it might be good to display the last buffer of output in case there's no output for a given duration?\r\n\r\nFor this it likely needs to keep track of the last e.g. 1000 bytes of output always.\r\n\r\nUpdate:\r\n`out_data_cb` and therefore `out_data_decide_throttle` are not called with no output in the first place.  This would require to have some additional timer then that would take care of this.",
